### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe the problem.

As per the documentation for [Minimal API custom binding](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/fundamentals/minimal-apis/parameter-binding#custom-binding), there a four methods that can be used to implement custom binding:
- public static bool TryParse(string value, out T result);
- public static bool TryParse(string value, IFormatProvider provider, out T result);
- public static ValueTask<T?> BindAsync(HttpContext context, ParameterInfo parameter);
- public static ValueTask<T?> BindAsync(HttpContext context);

The two TryParse methods can implemented using the [IParsable](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.iparsable-1) interface, but no interface exists for BindAsync. Although Minimal API does not require the interface, there would be benefit to having such an interface available when building out [OpenAPI definitions for custom bindings](https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/51218) or for use with source generators.

### Describe the solution you'd like

Due to the variations available for BindAsync, this would like need to be two different interfaces. Perhaps something like?

```csharp
public interface IBindable<TSelf>
    where TSelf : IBindable<TSelf>?
{
    static abstract ValueTask<TSelf?> BindAsync(HttpContext context);
}

public interface IBindableParameter<TSelf>
    where TSelf : IBindableParameter<TSelf>?
{
    static abstract ValueTask<TSelf?> BindAsync(HttpContext context, ParameterInfo parameter);
}
```

### Additional context

These interfaces can obviously be defined in our own code bases, but it'd be nice to see something like this be added to the SDK itself so we can't stop looking for the documentation or another place in our code where we've implemented this to remember what the specific signature needs to be.

